### 1. Generate RSA Key Pair (2048-bit)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/keys
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "keySize": 2048
}

### Store the response keyId and encryptedPrivateKeyBase64 for next requests

### 2. Fetch Public Key by ID
GET http://localhost:8080/api/keys/1

### 3. Create Digital Signature
POST http://localhost:8080/api/signatures
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "keyId": 1,
  "data": "This is the message to be signed",
  "encryptedPrivateKeyBase64": "PASTE_ENCRYPTED_PRIVATE_KEY_HERE"
}

### Store the response signatureId for verification

### 4a. Retrieve Signature Details
GET http://localhost:8080/api/signatures/1

### 4b. Verify Signature
POST http://localhost:8080/api/signatures/1?action=verify
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "signatureId": 1,
  "data": "This is the message to be signed"
}

### Test with wrong data (should fail verification)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/signatures/1?action=verify
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "signatureId": 1,
  "data": "This is different data"
}

### Generate 4096-bit key
POST http://localhost:8080/api/keys
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "keySize": 4096
}